solution:
According to Freundlich adsorption isotherm.
$$
\begin{aligned}
&\frac{\mathrm{x}}{\mathrm{m}}=\mathrm{kP}^{\frac{1}{\mathrm{n}}} \\
&\log _{10} \frac{\mathrm{x}}{\mathrm{m}}=\frac{1}{\mathrm{n}} \log _{10} \mathrm{P}+\log _{10} \mathrm{k}
\end{aligned}
$$
This is the equation of straight line of type $y=m x+c$
Hence slope is $1 / \mathrm{n}(\mathrm{m})$ and intercept is $\log _{\mathrm{e}} \mathrm{k}$.
